Description: Bust of a woman in profile to right, wearing a headscarf, possibly after Filippino Lippi Black chalk
Curator's comments: This is similar in type to Filippino Lippi, the exact prototype is not known. Not included in the Phillipps-Fenwick catalogue.
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: William Young Ottley (T. Philipe, 13.vi.1814/part of lot 739 as Filippino Lippi 'Two, one one [sic] leaf - a sybil sitting on clouds - ditto [i.e. metalpoint] on brown ground; and a lady's head, profile - black chalk')
Previous owner/ex-collection: Samuel Woodburn (Christie's, 4.vi.1860/part of lot 25 'The rest in Egypt, MASTELLETTA; and various', 12 in the lot, bt Phillipps £1-1-0)
